      <abstract>
        <p>Howard Goldberg reviews Tiefenbrunner's 2005 pinot bianco wine (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Germanic leitmotif found throughout Alto Adige (a k a South Tyrol) emerges in Tiefenbrunner's stylish 2005 pinot bianco, also labeled weissburgunder.</p>
        <p>Lean, tangy, awash in tropical nuances even though it comes from northernmost Italy, this austere, lingering white distantly resembles mineral-rich rieslings from Austria. It can accompany asparagus (a difficult match for wine), risotto, crustaceans and pork.</p>
      </block>
